Water CS Eugene Wamalwa has decided to shelve his political ambition &ldquo;to create time to campaign for Jubilee candidates in Western&rdquo;.Bumula MP Boniface Otsiula said the decision was made after a meeting with Bungoma and Trans Nzoia county officials.&ldquo;He will not be running for governor in either Nairobi or Trans Nzoia counties, but will instead support and campaign for jubilee aspirants in the two counties and across the country,&rdquo; he said.Speaking at Manani Primary School after distributing CDF funds, Otsiula said county leaders advised Wamalwa to serve in the government so &ldquo;we can have a direct link to the President and Deputy President.&rdquo;He said Wamalwa is the Luhyas &lsquo;eye&rsquo; in Jubilee. &ldquo;We cannot afford to lose his presence in the Jubilee government,&rdquo; Otsiula said.He added, &ldquo;We are optimistic Jubilee will be reelected. With this, Wamalwa is guaranteed of an even better plum ministerial post that will guarantee us a say in the government and we will also benefit from projects.&rdquo;Western keen on receiving goodiesOtsiula said Wamalwa will help the region receive goodies.Wamalwa hinted he might not run two weeks ago, during a meeting with Jubilee politicians in Webuye town.He said, &ldquo;I am going to campaign for Jubilee aspirants to win as many seats as possible.&rdquo;Wamalwa added, &ldquo;Bungoma Governor Kenneth Lusaka must retain his seat. The campaigns will be tough and will shake the opposition.&rdquo;